(secondQuint)A Study to Evaluate Alendronate Sodium /Vitamin D3 Combination Tablets(FOSAMAX PLUS) Versus Calcitriol in the Treatment of Osteoporosis in Postmenopausal Women in China (MK-0217A-264).

 This was a 6-month, randomized, open-label, active-comparator controlled, parallel-group study with a 6-month extension to evaluate the safety and efficacy of alendronate sodium 70 mg plus vitamin D3 5600 IU combination tablets versus calcitriol in the treatment of osteoporosis in postmenopausal women in China.

 Participants were randomly assigned to receive alendronate 70 mg plus vitamin D3 5600 IU combination tablet once weekly orally or calcitriol 0.

25 1/2g daily orally.

